People of Epe in Lagos State will as from Monday, 17th February, 2020, roll out drums to celebrate the 20 years on the throne of the Oloja of Epe Land, Oba Kamorudeen Ishola Animashaun. Family of the monarch disclosed this through a statement made available to newsmen in Lagos by a member, Lagos Lagos State House of Assembly, Hon. Abiodun Tobun; saying series of programmes had been lined up to make the one-week celebrations eventful. ALSO READ:Injustice, collapse of value system breeds insecurity ― Sultan of Sokoto According to the statement, commencing from Monday, 17th February, there will be a Medical Mission followed by a football match and symposium on Tuesday, 18th February, with a Traditional and Cultural Day holding the following day. The statement said Thursday has been slated for Community Party, with Jumat Service and Installation of Honorary Chiefs to hold on Friday, adding that the grand finale will hold on Saturday while thanksgiving comes up on Sunday, the 23rd of February, 2020. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE.